Entities:
account - accountId, customerId, country -------- Composition for balance and transaction, account - main entity, one to many
Balance - accountId, currency, availableAmount
Transaction - accountId, transactionId, amount, currency, description, direction, balanceAfterTransaction

EndPoints:
createAccount - IN (customerId, country, currencies || OUT (accountId, customerId, (currencies + available amount))
getAccount - IN (accountId) || OUT (accountId, customerId, (currencies + available amount))
createTransaction - IN (accountId, amount, currency, direction, description) || OUT (accountId, transactionId, amount, currency, direction, description, balanceAfterTransaction)
getTransactions - IN (accountId) || OUT (accountId, transactionId, amount, currency, direction, description)

Rules:
currencies, 1 of: EUR, USD, SEK, GBP
directions, 1 of: IN/OUT
amount must be positive
description required
insufficient balance
account exists
balance for request currency must exist

DB:
accounts - accountId (primary key) , customerId, country (countryCode: EE/DE/RU/etc...)
balances - accountId (foreign key), balanceId (primary key), currency (USD/EUR/SEK/GBP), availableAmount (Decimal) || unique (accountId + currency)
transactions - accountId (foreign key), transactionId (primary key), amount (Decimal), currency (USD/EUR/SEK/GBP), description, direction (IN/OUT), balanceAfterTransaction (Decimal)
EVERYTHING NOTNULL!!!! AMOUNTS > 0!!!!

EndPoint logic:
1. createAccount
request validation - DB generates accountId - create balance for each currency (basic amount: 0) - RABBITMQ event - response
2. getAccount
request validation - find account by accountId - find balances by accountId - response
3. createTransaction
request validation - find account - find balance by accountId + validate business rules + currency - update balance - create transaction - RABBITMQ event - response
4. getTransactions
request validation - find transactions by accountId - response

validation - check if exists, check if valid

Errors:
1. createAccount
invalid/null/not unique currency - Deny request
invalid/null country (ONLY COUNTRY CODE) - Deny request
invalid/null customerId - Deny request
2. getAccount
invalid/null accountId - Deny request
3. createTransaction
invalid/null accountId - Deny request
invalid/null amount (amount <= 0) - Deny request
invalid/null currency (ONLY GBP, EUR, USD, SEK) - Deny request
invalid/null direction (ONLY IN/OUT) - Deny request
null/empty description - Deny request
balance in currency{currency} not exists - Deny request
insufficient balance - Deny request
4. getTransactions
invalid/null accountId - Deny request

